l size stage  balcony and orchestra levels  a professional sound proofing system  and a highly effective communications network  Its design allows for multi functional use as an arts theater for cadet and community performances and as a beautiful venue for large lectures and other presentations  These facilities are complemented by a variety of well appointed and technologically advanced breakout meeting rooms of flexible design  a multi purpose assembly hall to accommodate up to 700 people in a banquet setting  and the Hall of Valor  a reflective space commemorating the service and sacrifice of VMI alumni in times of war  If you would like to find out more about scheduling an event at Marshall Hall please contact  Mrs  Ronda Dove Ph   540  464 7361 Fax   540  464 7396    VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Marshall Hall  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institut